      "span_text": "Blockade of thermal nociception was assessed using a modified hot plate test, similar to what we have used previously in studies of peripheral nerve blockade. 25 Hind paws were exposed in sequence (left then right) to a hot plate (model 39D hot plate analgesia meter; IITC Inc., Woodland Hills, CA) at 52°C for P7 and P14 pups and 56°C for P21 adolescents."
